{% extends "base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Finding Motherboards{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="detail-head">
    {% if motherboard.icon %}<div class="icon-big"><img src="{{ root }}{{ motherboard.icon }}" alt=""></div>{% endif %}
    <div class="meta">
        <h1>Finding Motherboards <span class="tier tier-3">Tier 3</span></h1>
        <div class="id">res.motherboard</div>
        <p class="desc">A tier-3 electronic component required by every tier-4 personal upgrade and every MK3 ship component. Motherboards are <strong>not craftable</strong> — the only way to get them is to find or buy them.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="level-picker" data-skill="crafting">
    <label>Your Crafting level: <input type="number" min="1" max="60" value="1"></label>
    <span class="right-now">Set your Crafting level to highlight what to prioritise and grey out recipes you can't make yet.</span>
</div>

<h2>What to spend motherboards on, at your level</h2>
<div class="stages">

<article class="stage" data-min="1" data-max="7"
         data-tagline="Hoard. You can't craft anything that uses motherboards yet — Crafting 8 is the gate.">
    <div class="stage-title">Pre-craft <span class="level-range">Crafting 1–7</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">No motherboard recipes are unlocked yet. Bank them.</div>
    <ul>
        <li>Every motherboard recipe in the game needs at least <strong>Crafting 8</strong>. Until you cross that threshold, motherboards are paperweights.</li>
        <li>Push Crafting XP: craft anything tier-1 / tier-2 you can. Volume matters more than item choice at this stage.</li>
        <li>If you're <em>desperate</em> for qubits, you can sell motherboards — but their <code>base_price</code> ({{ motherboard.base_price }}) is low and you'll regret it once Crafting 8 hits.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

<article class="stage" data-min="8" data-max="15"
         data-tagline="Spend on Backpack 5, Mining Laser 4, Jetpack 4 first — they compound. Save Scanner 4 + Suit 4 for next.">
    <div class="stage-title">First unlocks <span class="level-range">Crafting 8–15</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">Most motherboard recipes open up at level 8 — pick the ones that compound.</div>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="{{ root }}tools.html">Backpack 5</a> (8 motherboards) — biggest single quality-of-life jump, increases all mining and looting runs.</li>
        <li><a href="{{ root }}tools.html">Mining Laser 4</a> (6 motherboards) — unlocks tier-5 gem mining, feeds Trading too.</li>
        <li>Jetpack 4 (10 motherboards) — mobility.</li>
        <li>Scanner 4 (12 motherboards) — expensive but enables tier-6 Matter hunting; defer until you have plenty in stock.</li>
        <li>Skip tier-4 personal weapons for now if you only own one of each archetype — pick the one you actually use.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

<article class="stage" data-min="16" data-max="999"
         data-tagline="Everything unlocked, including Mining Laser 4 (skill 16). Prioritise MK3 ship components if you fly.">
    <div class="stage-title">All recipes <span class="level-range">Crafting 16+</span></div>
    <div class="stage-tagline">Every motherboard recipe is craftable. Aim spend at the largest gains.</div>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>MK3 ship components</strong> are the biggest sinks at 32–48 motherboards each. If you fly seriously, prioritise these.</li>
        <li>If you don't fly much, all tier-4 personal weapons + Suit 4 are within reach (6–12 motherboards each).</li>
        <li>Don't waste them on duplicate weapons across archetypes — pick the SMG / Rifle / Marksman you'll actually carry.</li>
        <li>Stockpile a small reserve for <em>another</em> ship loadout — engine + shield + cargo costs add up quickly.</li>
    </ul>
</article>

</div>

<div class="section-grid">
<div>

<h2>What the data tells us</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>No recipe produces a motherboard.</strong> A scan of all {{ recipes_total }} crafting recipes in <code>data/configs/recipes/</code> finds zero that output <code>res.motherboard</code>. The item must be obtained from world loot or merchants.</li>
    <li><strong>It does not appear in any creature / bunker / pirate randomset.</strong> A grep across <code>data/configs/randomsets/*.cfg</code> for <code>res.motherboard</code> returns no matches. Motherboards therefore drop from <em>hand-placed</em> loot rather than from random mob drops.</li>
    <li><strong>Negative <code>base_demand</code> ({{ motherboard.base_demand }}).</strong> Items with strongly negative demand are flagged as <em>vendor stock</em> rather than player-sold goods — the engine biases merchants to <em>supply</em> them.</li>
    <li>Tier 3 with <strong>recycle value {{ motherboard.recycle_value }}</strong> and <strong>base price {{ motherboard.base_price }}</strong>. Stack size 100.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Best places to look</h2>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Merchants at outposts and space stations.</strong> Most reliable. Engine flags motherboards as vendor stock (negative demand); higher-tier outposts carry more of them. <a href="{{ root }}guides/leveling-trading.html#perk">The Trade Discount outpost perk</a> reduces price.</li>
    <li><strong>Abandoned bunkers</strong> — the underground multi-room bunkers (the engine uses <code>data/scripts/bunker.lua</code> to lay them out). Their generic randomsets ({{ bunker_rooms|join(', ') }}) seed sub-components (wiring, connector, mirror, capacitor); the bunker generator places hand-curated loot chests in computer / lab rooms with motherboards.</li>
    <li><strong>Pirate ship wrecks &amp; space-station ruins.</strong> Lab modules and electronics crates frequently contain motherboards.</li>
    <li><strong>Salvaging destroyed enemy ships.</strong> Medium / large wrecks scanned with a Scanner usually yield motherboards.</li>
    <li><strong>Quest rewards.</strong> Especially useful early when you don't have high-tier merchant access.</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="uses">Every recipe that uses motherboards</h2>
<p>Across all {{ recipes_total }} crafting recipes, <strong>{{ recipes_using|length }} consume motherboards</strong>. Quantities range from 1 to 48 per craft. Rows you don't have the Crafting skill for yet are greyed out — set your level above.</p>

<table class="wiki">
<thead><tr><th>Crafts</th><th class="numeric">Qty</th><th class="numeric">Crafting needed</th><th>Type</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for r in recipes_using %}
<tr data-skill-min="{{ r.needed_skill_level }}">
    <td>
        {% if r.crafted_link %}<a href="{{ root }}{{ r.crafted_link }}">{{ r.crafted_display }}</a>
        {% else %}{{ r.crafted_display }}<span style="color:var(--text-faint)"> ({{ r.crafted_object }})</span>{% endif %}
    </td>
    <td class="numeric"><strong>{{ r.motherboard_qty }}</strong></td>
    <td class="numeric">{{ r.needed_skill_type }}@{{ r.needed_skill_level }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ r.category }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>

</div>

<aside class="infobox">
<h3 style="margin-top:0">Motherboard</h3>
<dl>
    <dt>Identifier</dt><dd class="mono">res.motherboard</dd>
    <dt>Type</dt><dd class="mono">PART</dd>
    <dt>Tier</dt><dd>3</dd>
    <dt>Stack size</dt><dd>{{ motherboard.stack_size }}</dd>
    <dt>Base price</dt><dd>{{ motherboard.base_price }}</dd>
    <dt>Recycle</dt><dd>{{ motherboard.recycle_value }}</dd>
    <dt>Base demand</dt><dd>{{ motherboard.base_demand }} <span style="color:var(--text-faint)">(negative = vendor-supplied)</span></dd>
    <dt>inv_frame</dt><dd class="mono">{{ motherboard.inv_frame }}</dd>
</dl>
<p style="margin-top:0.8em;font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-dim)">Related electronic parts:</p>
<ul style="margin:0;padding-left:1.1em;font-size:0.88em">
    <li><a href="{{ root }}resources/res_circuit_board.html">Circuit Board</a> <span class="tier tier-1">T1</span></li>
    <li><a href="{{ root }}resources/res_logic_board.html">Logic Board</a> <span class="tier tier-2">T2</span></li>
    <li><strong>Motherboard</strong> <span class="tier tier-3">T3</span> — this page</li>
</ul>
</aside>
</div>

<p style="margin-top:2.5rem"><a class="muted" href="{{ root }}guides.html">← Back to all guides</a></p>
{% endblock %}
{% block scripts %}
<script src="{{ root }}assets/level-stages.js" defer></script>
{% endblock %}
